The paper deals with learning from demonstrations, which is a common topic in machine learning and artificial intelligence. The focus is on transfer learning under sensor-shifts, which involves understanding the differences between sensory inputs. This suggests that the paper could belong to the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), robotics (cs.RO), computer vision (cs.CV), and systems and control (cs.SY).
